  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Specific form of\ncellulitis\ninvolving the superficial levels of the dermis and subcutaneous tissues (including lymphatics)\n[1]\nMajority of cases caused by\nstreptococcus\n[1]\n[2]\nHowever, recent data indicates\nS. aureus\n(specifically, CA-MRSA) is a rising cause.\nUsually affects lower extremities (face is also common)\n[3]",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "cellulitis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Cellulitis"
        },
        {
          "text": "streptococcus",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Streptococcus"
        },
        {
          "text": "S. aureus",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/S._aureus"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Rash\nLocal erythema, warmth, swelling\nWell demarcated and raised border\n[1]\nCan be accompanied by\nfever\n, chills, malaise,\nheadache\n,\nnausea/vomiting",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
